message.content:
If Harmony folds a letter-size paper three times, it will be reduced to 1/8th of its original size each time, so the final product would be 1/8th of the original size. This means that she creates 8 smaller note papers from one sheet of paper. If she staples them together, she can make a notepad with 8 pages.

If someone writes ten notes per day, and each notepad has 8 pages, then one notepad will last for 8 days before it is filled up completely.
